{"type": "article", "id": 37486, "title": "戴上这些眼罩，做一次画中人｜这个设计了不起", "description": "我们每天都为你推荐几个最近发现的好设计。", "date": "2017-02-06T00:03:19Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [{"id": 271, "name": "工业设计"}, {"id": 37359, "name": "Castor Design"}, {"id": 37360, "name": "Socio Design"}, {"id": 37361, "name": "Lesha Limonov"}, {"id": 37362, "name": "Adam Gill"}, {"id": 37363, "name": "Duy Anh Nhan Duc"}, {"id": 37364, "name": "Micaella Pedros"}], "category": 17, "column": 38, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 12, "praise_count": 154, "image": "img/article/article_show/20170205232920BH6Rm3YpAgh7GPUS.jpg", "contents": "<p>        <style type=\"text/css\"> p.p1 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p2 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 27.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} p.p3 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636} p.p4 {margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; line-height: 32.0px; font: 18.0px 'PingFang SC'; color: #363636; min-height: 25.0px} span.s1 {font-kerning: none} span.s2 {font-kerning: none; color: #323333} </style>  </p><p>「这个设计了不起」的微信公众号上线啦，直接搜索「BestDesign」或是「Qthings」就可以订阅，关注我们每日发现的新鲜好设计。</p><h3>Masterpieces never sleep! by Lesha Limonov</h3><p><a href=\"https://www.rijksmuseum.nl/en/rijksstudio-award\" rel=\"nofollow\">International Rijksstudio award</a> 是荷兰阿姆斯特丹国立博物馆（Rijksmuseum）创立于 2013 的设计比赛，欢迎来自世界各地的设计师以馆藏为灵感进行创作。这套名为 <a href=\"https://www.behance.net/gallery/47375879/Masterpieces-never-sleepConcept-for-Rijksmuseum\" rel=\"nofollow\">Masterpieces never sleep!</a> 的眼罩就是由白俄罗斯的 <a href=\"http://levsha-design.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Lesha Limonov</a> 以“即便到了夜晚，画中人还是醒着”为概念设计的，他将包括《夜巡》和梵高自画像在内的六幅画作中的眼睛放大，印在了眼罩上。它们的包装是厚纸板制成的圆筒，一头是对应的单眼，另一头是作品名。绕圆筒一周的标签上则印有作品的局部，Limonov 还特意用黄色虚线勾勒出了双眼的部分解释产品用途。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205232949jvaN259myeALrOET.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562347\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205232949CEGmJNBhc8UfVPRD.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563570\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205232949mKzGr4SRAVgpFdUW.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562347\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205232950HmuAL3BPZoi4hJOV.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563570\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205232950rPE15BcjGwKM4T2y.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.563570\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><h3>60 Second Salad Maker by Craig Wenger &amp; David Turover</h3><p>曾经推出过<a href=\"http://www.nocleanaquariums.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">免换水水族箱</a>的 Craig Wenger 和 David Turover 最近又带来了一款想让生活变得更轻松的厨具 60 Second Salad Maker，正如它的字面意思，这个碗状过滤器可以让制作沙拉的过程缩短到 60 秒的时间内。它的原理其实就是一口气将所有食材集合在一起，利用条状的镂空部分和碗倒扣之后波浪形状的边缘，让人可以随心所欲地在多个方向进行均匀地切割。相比切好再混合的来回操作，这个制作器可以有效避免汁液飞溅的情况，在切割和旋转之间一个只需要加调料的沙拉就完成了。你可以最低价 14 美元通过<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/930441187/60-second-salad-maker-healthy-fresh-salads-made-ea\" rel=\"nofollow\">链接</a>参与众筹。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233023Q97VUdoBJ1zksyKw.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.407353\" data-format=\"png\" class=\"\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201702052330244qAu5zX26JM7jsRP.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562500\" data-format=\"gif\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233024T8yWK415kMQqn9gd.png\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.867647\" data-format=\"png\">\n</figure></div><h3>Big Switch by Castor Design</h3><p>当不少设计师忙着用触摸感应或是其他手段把台灯开关“弄没”的时候，加拿大多伦多的 <a href=\"http://castordesign.ca/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Castor Design</a> 工作室利用这盏名为 Big Switch 表达了异议，光是从它直白的名字中你就能体会到设计师的态度。为了强调开关的存在感，这些位于灯柱顶部的新月形按钮采用了不同于其他部分的醒目颜色，配合台灯紧凑圆润的造型，营造出一种卡通感，看起来相当活泼可爱。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/201702052331078FtjOweT6kxdMl49.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667188\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233105vXp5ysHCk0LogMQN.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233105sA8937SacRfCNMZJ.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666667\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233105j9LXAED7H1cuC06T.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.654321\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><h3>Beau Cacao by Adam Gill &amp; Socio Design</h3><p><a href=\"http://www.beaucacao.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Beau Cacao</a> 是一个来自英国伦敦的巧克力品牌，创始人 Bo San Cheung 和 Thomas Delcour 同为旅行和美食爱好者，也正是在旅途中为当地人的热情和可可豆的品质所折服，让他们最终选择直接与马来西亚的可可豆农进行合作。为了体现出产地特色，他们委托好友 <a href=\"http://adamgill.tv/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Adam Gill</a> 以马来西亚独特的织物风格为灵感设计了充满立体感的几何<a href=\"http://adamgill.tv/beau-cacao-bar-design\" rel=\"nofollow\">模具</a>。负责包装设计的 <a href=\"http://sociodesign.co.uk/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Socio Design</a> 则延续了这种风格，用丰富的线条营造出异域的气质。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233211hrtKxR9NpkXJl2j0.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562500\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233212aNC0YKtk6FizsL7j.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.562500\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233211ZBN4JEYgPsUyol9K.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.664844\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233211WduV7gkpyLhUlF4b.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.664844\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><h3>The Imaginary Herbarium by Duy Anh Nhan Duc</h3><p>现居法国的 <a href=\"http://www.duyanhnhanduc.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Duy Anh Nhan Duc</a> 是一名植物艺术家，当你看到这些小心翼翼摆放而成的作品后，除了有想去吹一下蒲公英的冲动之外，感受更多的或许还是他的耐心。当泛着淡黄色的茸毛微微拂动起来，这些本身相当脆弱的蒲公英又好像传递出一种宁静而有力的感觉。他的个人展 The <a href=\"http://www.galeriebettina.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Imaginary Herbarium</a> 最近正在巴黎的 Bettina 画廊展出，将持续到 2 月 15 日。如果你对他的作品感兴趣的话，还可以关注他的 <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/duyanhnhanduc/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Instagram</a>。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233358OExC1omceLGU0B95.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.000000\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233357ndEB0gVXNcZKROes.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233357SkjrT7oQGsFNW3hc.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.667000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233357WY6mUEOI0FLNCynk.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.666000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233358JS2GsrdX1ajfKQh0.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.500000\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><h3>Joining Bottles by Micaella Pedros</h3><p>如何改造废弃的塑料制品是很多设计师热衷于探索的主题，去年毕业于皇家艺术学院的产品设计师 <a href=\"http://micaellapedros.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Micaella Pedros</a> 用这个名为 <a href=\"http://joiningbottles.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Joining Bottles</a> 的项目展示了废物利用的另一种可能性。现居英国伦敦的 Pedros 在街头收集废弃的塑料瓶，裁开之后将它们套在木头的接缝处进行加热，以此作为五金件的替代品。尽管这些 DIY 家具看起来都比较简陋，她还是希望能通过这一块块“补丁”让更多人能够重新思考废弃塑料瓶的价值。</p><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233246jXGghUBKrYNuF7Qb.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.518462\" data-format=\"jpeg\" class=\"\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233246EIUnjMG4rlpDxWwS.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.963077\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233245gqbYBmVvUw0DhrpI.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.561644\" data-format=\"gif\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233246bXLWTUkgpsBwY9qI.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.561644\" data-format=\"gif\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin: 0px;\" class=\"\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233247ihoTqICY6UDpL1dX.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.561644\" data-format=\"gif\">\n</figure></div><div class=\"com-insert-images\"><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20170205233246UXCtA07JsgdFnzGY.gif\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.561644\" data-format=\"gif\">\n</figure></div>"}